WEBVTT

00:00:06.770 --> 00:00:17.520 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Lovingly Jehovah
‎Made provision through his Son

00:00:17.520 --> 00:00:28.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎For our sins to be forgiven
‎And for death to be undone.

00:00:28.854 --> 00:00:40.312 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎If we truly are repentant,
‎His forgiveness we can claim

00:00:40.312 --> 00:00:52.104 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎On the basis of Christ’s ransom,
‎Asking pardon in his name.

00:00:52.104 --> 00:01:03.395 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎We receive such mercy
‎When we act like God above

00:01:03.395 --> 00:01:14.604 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎And forgive each other freely,
‎Showing empathy and love.

00:01:14.604 --> 00:01:26.312 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Putting up with one another,
‎Putting hurtfulness away;

00:01:26.312 --> 00:01:38.145 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Showing honor to our brother,
‎Showing love’s surpassing way.

00:01:41.062 --> 00:01:52.104 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Mercy is a virtue
‎That we all should cultivate.

00:01:52.104 --> 00:02:03.229 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎It will keep us from resentment,
‎From the bitterness of hate.

00:02:03.229 --> 00:02:14.895 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎When we imitate Jehovah,
‎Who is unsurpassed in love,

00:02:14.895 --> 00:02:29.270 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎We will truly be forgiving;
‎We will be like God above.

